  "prompt": "I am an average student preparing for the IIT-JEE. Which test series is the best for me for free?",
  "response": "As an average student preparing for the IIT-JEE, it's great that you're looking for resources to help you improve. While there are many paid test series available, here are some free resources that can be beneficial:\n\n1. **NTA's Official Website (nta.ac.in)**\n   - The National Testing Agency (NTA) often releases free mock tests and sample papers for JEE Main. These are valuable as they are from the official source and can give you a good idea of the exam pattern.\n\n2. **JEE Main Mock Tests by Embibe**\n   - Embibe offers free mock tests for JEE Main, which are designed to simulate the actual exam environment. They also provide detailed performance analysis to help you understand your strengths and weaknesses.\n\n3. **Free IIT-JEE Test Series by Vedantu**\n   - Vedantu provides free test series for JEE aspirants. These tests are designed by experienced educators and can help you gauge your preparation level.\n\n4. **Khan Academy (khanacademy.org)**\n   - While Khan Academy doesn't offer a specific JEE test series, it has a wealth of free resources for math and physics that are aligned with the JEE syllabus. You can use these to strengthen your foundational knowledge.\n\n5. **eSaral (esaral.com)**\n   - eSaral offers free mock tests and practice questions for JEE aspirants. The platform is user-friendly and can be a good addition to your preparation strategy.\n\n6. **Toppr (toppr.com)**\n   - Toppr provides free JEE mock tests and practice papers. They also offer detailed solutions and performance analytics to help you track your progress.\n\nWhen using these free resources, make sure to:\n- Take the tests seriously and simulate exam conditions as much as possible.\n- Analyze your performance to identify areas that need improvement.\n- Use the resources consistently to build a strong preparation routine.\n\nRemember, the key to success in JEE is consistent practice and a strong understanding of concepts. Good luck with your preparation!",
